    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A low-molecular-weight adhesive made from a solution of degraded or denatured collagen in water. The protein content in animal glue is less pure and darker in color than gelatin.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
